On World Press Freedom Day, the President of the United States reaffirms the importance of freedom of expression, assembly, and association. The President emphasizes the need to protect these fundamental freedoms and recognizes the journalists who work tirelessly to uphold them, even at great personal risk. The President also highlights the alarming number of journalists who have been killed or imprisoned for reporting the truth. He condemns governments that hinder press freedom and mentions specific countries where press freedoms are severely restricted. The President acknowledges the positive role that new media tools can play in empowering citizens but cautions against their potential for censorship. He emphasizes that a free press is essential for successful and accountable governance. On this day, the President honors the journalists who have lost their lives in pursuit of the truth and recognizes their contribution to strengthening democratic governance worldwide.